<TITLE> UK lauds judiciary separation </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 23 (bdnews24.com)  Britain has praised the caretaker government's ongoing move to separate the judiciary from the executive in a bid to consolidate democratic institutions. "Separation of the judiciary from the executive is a very positive step of the caretaker government in order to create sustainable democratic institutions in Bangladesh," British foreign secretary David Miliband told foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury Thursday on the sidelines of the Commonwealth Summit in Uganda. The British foreign secretary praised the reform measures undertaken by the caretaker government, according to foreign ministry officials in Kampala. Miliband expressed deep sympathy for the destruction caused by Cyclone Sidr and assured the foreign adviser of all possible help in relief and rehabilitation of cyclone survivors. The two foreign ministers also discussed the political situation in Pakistan and Myanmar. bdnews
